cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with the classification of musical instrument sounds using deep learning techniques. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper proposes a new method for feature extraction from musical instrument sounds using multiresolution recurrence plots (MRPs) that contain phase information. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for classification of musical instrument sounds. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new approach for feature fusion using MRPs and spectrogram images to improve the performance of the classifier system. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the classification of musical instrument sounds, which is a multimedia application.
